FOOTBALL has seen some wild celebrations in the last week! And who wouldn&rsquo;t want to be part of the celebrations of victorious teams from across the world as they clinched their league titles? Sunday saw the English Premier League season draw to a close with Arsenal missing out on the top four and Uefa Champions League football for the first time in 20 years as Liverpool won a place among Europe&rsquo;s elite. But the big news broke last week already when Chelsea clinched the title &ndash; without Jose Mourinho.Real Madrid won their first La Liga title since 2012 thanks to a final day victory at Malaga. Cristiano Ronaldo scored early on to settle the nerves, latching onto Isco&rsquo;s through ball to step around Carlos Kameni and tap into an empty net. Karim Benzema added their second goal.Juventus claimed a record sixth straight Italian Serie A title with a 3-0 win over relegation-threatened Crotone in the penultimate round on Sunday. Bidvest Wits took home the SA PSL title for the first time in history.